'''資訊超載'''（{{Lang-en|information overload}}）是指接受太多[[資訊|資訊]]，反而影響正常的[[理解|理解]]與[[決策|決策]]<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Yang, CC.|first1=Chen, Hsinchun|last2=Honga, Kay|date=2003|title=Visualization of Large Category Map for Internet Browsing|url=http://www.cis.drexel.edu/faculty/cyang/papers/yang2003f.pdf|journal=Decision Support Systems|volume=35|issue=1|pages=89–102|doi=10.1016/S0167-9236(02)00101-X|hdl=10150/106272}}</ref>，它往往於日常信息過多有關。「資訊超載」一詞最早於1962年由管理學和資訊科學的學者開始使用；1964年，Bertram Gross在他的《The Managing of Organizations》中使用了該詞<ref>{{cite book|title=The Managing Organizations: The Administrative Struggle, vol 2|last=Gross|first=Bertram, M.|year=1964|pages=856ff}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Levy |first1=Daniel |editor1-last=Himma |editor1-first=Kenneth Himar |editor2-last=Tavani |editor2-first=Herman T. |title=The Handbook of Information and Computer Ethics |date=2008 |publisher=Wiley & Sons |location=Hoboken |isbn=978-0-471-79959-7 |page=502 |url=https://www.academia.edu/download/4721200/the-handbook-of-information-and-computer-ethics.pdf#page=533 |chapter=Information Overload}}</ref>；1970年，Alvin Toffler在他的著作《{{Link-en|Future Shock|未来冲击}}》中也使用了該詞語，進一步推廣了這一概念。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.interaction-design.org/literature/article/information-overload-why-it-matters-and-how-to-combat-it|title=Information Overload, Why it Matters and How to Combat It|website=Interaction Design Foundation|access-date=August 1, 2018}}</ref>Speier等人（1999）認為，如果輸入的資訊超過處理能力，就會發生資訊超載，這很可能會降低決策的品質。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Speier |first1=Cheri |last2=Valacich |first2=Joseph S. |last3=Vessey |first3=Iris |title=The Influence of Task Interruption on Individual Decision Making: An Information Overload Perspective |journal=Decision Sciences |date=March 1999 |volume=30 |issue=2 |pages=337–360 |doi=10.1111/j.1540-5915.1999.tb01613.x}}</ref>

Roetzel（2019）提出了該概念側重時間和資源方面的新定義。他指出，當一個決策者得到多組資訊，如複雜度、數量和矛盾等資訊時，由於個人處理所有資訊並做出最佳決策的稀缺資源的限制，其決策的品質會降低。<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Roetzel|first=Peter Gordon|date=2019|title=Information overload in the information age: a review of the literature from business administration, business psychology, and related disciplines with a bibliometric approach and framework development|journal=Business Research|volume=12|issue=2|pages=479–522|language=en|doi=10.1007/s40685-018-0069-z|doi-access=free}}</ref>

現代[[信息技术|信息技术]]在很多層面上都是資訊超載的主要驅動因素之一，包括資訊生產的數量上、資訊傳播的容易程度上，以及受眾的廣度上。[[社群媒體|社群媒體]]和[[注意力經濟|注意力經濟]]的興起進一步加劇了長期存在的技術因素，從而助長了{{Tsl|en|attention theft|注意力盜用}}的問題。<ref name="Wired">{{cite news |last1=Wu |first1=Tim |authorlink=Tim Wu |title=The Crisis of Attention Theft—Ads That Steal Your Time for Nothing in Return |url=https://www.wired.com/2017/04/forcing-ads-captive-audience-attention-theft-crime/ |access-date=9 August 2021 |work=Wired |date=April 14, 2017}}</ref><ref name="IEEE">{{cite news |last1=McFedries |first1=Paul |title=Stop, Attention Thief! |url=https://spectrum.ieee.org/stop-attention-thief |access-date=9 August 2021 |work=[[IEEE综览|IEEE Spectrum]] |publisher=[[电气电子工程师学会|Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]] |date=22 May 2014 |language=en}}</ref>在網絡技術、資訊學、[[网络文化|网络文化]]的時代，資訊超載與過度接觸、過度瀏覽資訊，以及輸入大量資訊和資料有關。

